 i am currently working on an A-level in Design and Technology and i have chosen to design a new concept in games console control pads, i am working on the design of a PS2 controller whith the new concepts of being able to split the controller in two (don't ask me why, but it sounds like a good idea) and using a track ball instead of the right stick (i find it hard to control FPSs with the sticks and thought you might get more control with a track ball) i was hoping people could give me their views on my work. e.g aesthetics, views on the new concepts and if you think it has potential for manufacture etc.<br>
The model was made by vacuum forming plastic over moulds that i designed myself, holes were then made in the plastic an buttons from existing control pads and a track ball were added.<br>
Pictures of the model can be found at this site:<br>
<br>
www.freewebs.com/helpmeout<br>
<br>
Sorry about the crappy site, i made it in about 5 mins.<br>
Thanks in advance for any feedback. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=themightyservo>The Mighty Servo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/31/03 12:15:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=639.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   well...</span><hr size=1> I dunno. I personally don't think it'd be that great. The way that you've changed the way that the analog sticks work like that means that it'd be really limited to certain games. The layout would be nigh worthless for fighters (2D really) and driving games. Not to say that it couldn't have its uses...the Gamecube controller is also horrible for 2D fighters, but it's quite good for other types of games. Even then, the layout does deviate from the standard to the point that the carefully thought out control layouts might not work too well. Possibly though, fps fans would take to it (seems like you've designed around that). <br>
I tend to avoid fps games on consoles whenever possibly, mostly because of the control issues. However, the PS2 can accept a standard USB keyboard and mouse...borrowed from your computer or can be bought for a total of $30-40. Your controller would likely cost near that, especially with inclusion of a trackball (remember the rumble motors and all that are standard now).  The idea of a trackball itself on a controller isn't bad. It's been done before <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.theapplecollection.com/design/macproto/Pippin.html">www.theapplecollection.co...ippin.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> but never mainstream. I dunno about fps control with one, but perhaps for WebTV for TiVO type use it'd be sweet. Next gen consoles might have that functionality too. Then again, I get my butt kicked by our Sysadmin when playing at Lan parties, and his weapon of choice is one of those Trackman marble dealies....<br>
As for the splitting...it just doesn't seem to be that useful. Cool perhaps...but hard to say if it'd make things easier or harder. When together it sorta reminds me of the old NeGCon <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.vidgames.com/ps/hardware/negcon.html">www.vidgames.com/ps/hardware/negcon.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> but without the functionality of that device (which might be useful to put in rather than splitting). <br>
One thing that seems to be apparent from your design (and other specialized designs out there like the ASCII fighter pads) is that people want controllers to be more specific to their favorite games. I'd say that rather than making one that simply splits, or one that is tailored only to your tastes, to perhaps try making a controller that can be reconfigured. Something like <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.tomshardware.com/game/20030329/index.html">www.tomshardware.com/game...index.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> only for consoles. So maybe Joe Gamer can go buy a trackball module to plug into his PS2 controller right analog control slot for like $5 rather than buy a $30 controller to have that functionality. Allow fighter fans to put blank parts in there instead of having bulk sticks in the way (and maybe swap in a 2X3 button config a la Saturn instead of the 2X2 diamond). Possibly you could just make half the controller pop off to do this too, to remain similar to your design. <br>
At the very least, the start/select buttons should be over the trackball and control pad (more similar to the regular PS2 pad). They're very much in a position to accidentally get hit, like the Black and White buttons on the XBox controller S. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trunxx647>Trunxx647</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/2/03 7:32:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=639.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Yeah...but...</span><hr size=1> Yeah, he summed it up, but if you're going to have a trackball, put it on the other side. Hitting the certain buttons while moving the trackball could be a chore. And keep at least one analog stick, but make it more Dreamcast-ish. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=639.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=639.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=639.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.emailToFriend?topicID=639.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.threadControl?topicID=639.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professi